Solar Calorie Counter Data Deletion Request Steps.
solarinum

1. From the home page of the app, navigate to settings by pressing the gear icon.

2. Press the "Delete Data" button towards the bottom of the page. 

3. Press confirm.

Your data is now deleted.
You will be returned to an empty home calendar.
If an error is encountered, or for further questions, please fill out this form:
https://forms.gle/DUqXSBtb8TcRNq798


Types of data kept:
  - custom foods
    - food name (text)
    - calories (integer)
    - grams of protein (integer)
  - meals logged
    - calories (integer)
    - grams of protein (integer)
    - notes (text)
    - timestamp (Firestore Timestamp)
    - custom foods
    - quantity for each food (integer)
  - day
    - calories (integer)
    - grams of protein (integer)
    - custom meals
    - timestamp (Firestore Timestamp)
  - home calendar starting hour (integer)

Types of data deleted:
  - all.

Retention Period Following Deletion Request:
  - zero.

Interaction data is not collected.
Your Font Size, Background Theme, and Font Style preferences are not saved to any server or associated with your account.
Your provided feedback is not associated with your account.
